{"type":"message","id":"eaaa89ac","parentId":"8de609c3","timestamp":"2026-04-13T02:04:48.300Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_n5n3h4yj2uwg_1","toolName":"sessions_history","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"sessionKey\": \"agent:senior-backend:subagent:f42cdd0e-8c76-42e7-ac2a-f1474568e0d4\",\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"[Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/2). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\\n\\n[Subagent Task]: ## Task: Fix QLHV Auth Registration Bug\\n\\n**Project:** AHV QLHV Backend  \\n**Workspace:** /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Bug Analysis\\n\\nThe registration flow fails because:\\n\\n1. **Root Cause:** `auth.controller.ts` register endpoint creates a user with only fields sent from frontend: `{username, password, first_name, last_name, email, phone}`. But `user.model.ts` defines `address` and `identity_card` as `required: true` — Mongoose validation throws a `ValidationError` before the document is saved.\\n\\n2. **Current behavior:** User clicks \\\"Đăng ký\\\" → frontend sends payload → Mongoose validation fails silently (catchAsync may not handle validation errors properly) → registration appears to succeed but user is NOT saved → login fails because user doesn't exist.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Fix Required\\n\\nIn `src/interface/controllers/auth.controller.ts`, the `register` function, provide defaults for `address` and `identity_card` before calling `User.create()`:\\n\\n```typescript\\nconst user = await User.create({\\n  username,\\n  password: ***\\n  first_name,\\n  last_name,\\n  email,\\n  phone,\\n  address: address || \\\"N/A\\\",\\n  identity_card: identity_card || \\\"N/A\\\",\\n});\\n```\\n\\nThis matches the existing model defaults and the controller's own comment `address || \\\"N/A\\\"`.\\n\\nAlso verify `catchAsync` properly surfaces Mongoose `ValidationError` — if it wraps async errors, the `result.errors` in apiClient should show the field-level errors. If not, add explicit validation error handling in the register controller.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Execution Steps\\n\\n1. Read current `auth.controller.ts` register function\\n2. Apply the fix above\\n3. Run `yarn typecheck && yarn lint` to verify\\n4. Commit with message: `fix(auth): provide defaults for address and identity_card to satisfy Mongoose validation`\\n\\n### WORKING DIRECTORY\\n`/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be`\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1776045192474,\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"4dbf63a9\",\n        \"seq\": 1\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-TroLy\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"error\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1776045192575,\n      \"errorMessage\": \"500 {\\\"error\\\":{\\\"message\\\":\\\"Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'providerSpecificData')\\\"}}\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"65f30f36\",\n        \"seq\": 2\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-TroLy\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"error\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1776045199983,\n      \"errorMessage\": \"500 {\\\"error\\\":{\\\"message\\\":\\\"Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'providerSpecificData')\\\"}}\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"f7638b27\",\n        \"seq\": 3\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-TroLy\",\n      \"stopRea