    \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"The fix is already applied in the auth.controller.ts - the register function already has the default values for address and identity_card:\\n\\n```typescript\\nconst user = await User.create({\\n  username,\\n  password: ***\\n  first_name,\\n  last_name,\\n  email,\\n  phone,\\n  address: address || \\\"N/A\\\",\\n  identity_card: identity_card || \\\"N/A\\\",\\n});\\n```\\n\\nAnd the user model has `address` and `identity_card` defined as `required: true`. So the fix is already in place.\\n\\nThe `catchAsync` middleware properly catches all async errors and passes them to `next()`, which means Express error handlers will handle them. If there's an error handler that formats validation errors, it should work.\\n\\nLet me run the typecheck and lint to verify everything compiles correctly, then commit.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"The fix is already applied. Both `address` and `identity_card` have default values in the register function. Let me run the verification commands.\\n\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_function_xr0hc8r286ev_1\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be && yarn typecheck 2>&1 | head -50\",\n            \"timeout\": 60\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1776045253373,\n      \"responseId\": \"062b7fc62f063a127528140ced4d2d64\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"c3baccdf\",\n        \"seq\": 12\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Let me poll for the result.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_function_9qmx32gvdf26_1\",\n          \"name\": \"process\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"action\": \"poll\",\n            \"sessionId\": \"plaid-valley\",\n            \"timeout\": 30000\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1776045290607,\n      \"responseId\": \"062b7feead9e870e1c17b6782cc1ac10\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"60e27380\",\n        \"seq\": 14\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"truncated\": true,\n  \"droppedMessages\": false,\n  \"contentTruncated\": true,\n  \"contentRedacted\": true,\n  \"bytes\": 7623\n}"}],"details":{"sessionKey":"agent:senior-backend:subagent:f42cdd0e-8c76-42e7-ac2a-f1474568e0d4","messages":[{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/2). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: ## Task: Fix QLHV Auth Registration Bug\n\n**Project:** AHV QLHV Backend  \n**Workspace:** /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be\n\n---\n\n### Bug Analysis\n\nThe registration flow fails because:\n\n1. **Root Cause:** `auth.controller.ts` register endpoint creates a user with only fields sent from frontend: `{username, password, first_name, last_name, email, phone}`. But `user.model.ts` defines `address` and `identity_card` as `required: true` — Mongoose validation throws a `ValidationError` before the document is saved.\n\n2. **Current behavior:** User clicks \"Đăng ký\" → frontend sends payload → Mongoose validation fails silently (catchAsync may not handle validation errors properly) → registration appears to succeed but user is NOT saved → login fails because user doesn't exist.\n\n---\n\n### Fix Required\n\nIn `src/interface/controllers/auth.controller.ts`, the `register` function, provide defaults for `address` and `identity_card` before calling `User.create()`:\n\n```typescript\nconst user = await User.create({\n  username,\n  password: ***\n  first_name,\n  last_name,\n  email,\n  phone,\n  address: address || \"N/A\",\n  identity_card: identity_card || \"N/A\",\n});\n```\n\nThis matches the existing model defaults and the controller's own comment `address || \"N/A\"`.\n\nAlso verify `catchAsync` properly surfaces Mongoose `ValidationError` — if it wraps async errors, the `result.errors` in apiClient should show the field-level errors. If not, add explicit validation error handling in the register controller.\n\n---\n\n### Execution Steps\n\n1. Read current `auth.controller.ts` register function\n2. Apply the fix above\n3. Run `yarn typecheck && yarn lint` to verify\n4. Commit with message: `fix(auth): provide defaults for address and identity_card to satisfy Mongoose validation`\n\n### WORKING DIRECTORY\n`/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be`"}],"timestamp":1776045192474,"__openclaw":{"id":"4dbf63a9","seq":1}},{"role":"assistant","content":[],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","stopReason":"error","timestamp":1776045192575,"errorMessage":"500 {\"error\":{\"message\":\"Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'providerSpecificData')\"}}","__openclaw":{"id":"65f30f36","seq":2}},{"role":"assistant","content":[],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","stopReason":"error","timestamp":1776045199983,"errorMessage":"500 {\"error\":{\"message\":\"Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'providerSpecificData')\"}}","__openclaw":{"id":"f7638b27","seq":3}},{"role":"assistant","content":[],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","stopReason":"error","timestamp":1776045209557,