{"type":"message","id":"4758a890","parentId":"bbac0548","timestamp":"2026-04-13T03:23:20.806Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying that the license categories (hạng bằng) on the settings page is not loading data from the database. Let me look at the `LicenseCategoryManagement` component to understand what's happening. The `categories` prop is passed from `systemSettings?.license_categories || []` - but where does this data come from?\n\nLooking at the `fetchAllData` function, it calls `getSystemSettings()` which calls `apiClient('/settings')`. Let me check if there's a BE API endpoint that returns `license_categories`.\n\nThe BE `settings.controller.ts` uses `settingsService.getSettings(userId)` which reads from the settings repository. \n\nI need to check what's actually being returned by the settings endpoint and whether the license categories are even being populated there. The `license_categories` might be stored in a separate collection entirely, so I should trace through the BE to see where this data is supposed to come from.","thinkingSignature":"6d124e699fe7576526ba09b3a483197f02be76efc87380fada1515d380fe90f7"},{"type":"text","text":"Để tôi kiểm tra kỹ hơn — xem BE có API riêng cho license categories chưa.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dzcod3xivdh2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"license_categories\\|licensecategories\\|licensecategory\\|hang_bang\\|hangbang\" \\\n  ~/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src \\\n  --include=\"*.ts\" | grep -v \"node_modules\\|test\\|spec\" | grep -v \"\\.d\\.ts\" | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":11046,"output":325,"cacheRead":17809,"cacheWrite":12814,"totalTokens":41994,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776050582030,"responseId":"062b94975999eb85b52