{"type":"message","id":"9598b1fa","parentId":"b29d48b0","timestamp":"2026-04-13T03:23:49.415Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the architecture clearly:\n\n1. **Seed data**: `ultimate_seed.ts` inserts license categories into the `licensecategories` collection (not into `settings.license_categories`)\n2. **Settings model**: `settings.model.ts` has `license_categories: ILicenseCategory[]` as an embedded array in the settings document\n3. **LicenseCategoryModel**: separate collection `licensecategories` with fields: `name`, `code`, `description`\n\nThe problem is:\n- The FE reads `license_categories` from the `/settings` API → this reads from the `settings` collection → `settings.license_categories` might be empty\n\n\n- The actual license categories are stored in the `licensecategories` collection, so the settings API never returns them\n\nI need to fix this by either creating a dedicated endpoint to fetch all license categories from their collection and update the FE service accordingly, or embedding them in the settings response. Let me check the routes structure to see how these endpoints are organized.","thinkingSignature":"216be65212df3951a5b0dba021ba48870e1f5c32b81efb9f15bf57631ea2ce57"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rt0gm5jv3aec_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/interface/routes/index.ts"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rt0gm5jv3aec_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/interface/routes/"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":780,"output":298,"cacheRead":41559,"cacheWrite":1471,"totalTokens":44108,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776050620316,"responseId":"062b94bdf660aa8