{"type":"message","id":"6ff89532","parentId":"dcb7cfba","timestamp":"2026-04-13T03:24:42.188Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture:\n\n**FE `LicenseCategory` interface** (from `settingsService.ts`):\n```typescript\ninterface LicenseCategory {\n  id: string;\n  type: 'Ô tô' | 'Xe máy';\n  name: string;\n  fee: string;  // formatted like \"50.000đ\"\n  tags: string[];\n  inactive: string[];\n  dat: string | null;\n}\n```\n\n**BE `ILicenseCategory`** (from `license_category.model.ts`):\n```typescript\ninterface ILicenseCategory {\n  name: string;      // e.g. \"Hạng B1\"\n  code: string;      // e.g. \"B1\"\n  description?: string;\n}\n```\n\nThe BE stores license categories in a separate collection with just name, code, and description, but the FE expects a richer structure with type, fee, tags, inactive, and dat fields. The FE currently reads from `settings.license_categories` which is empty, so I need to either expand the BE model to include all FE fields or build an API endpoint that maps between the two structures.\n\nI'll create a dedicated `license-category.routes.ts` endpoint that reads from `LicenseCategoryModel` and maps it to the FE's expected format with all required fields. the data with all needed FE fields (`type`, `fee`, `tags`, etc.)\n\nActually, the cleanest approach for a quick fix:\n1. Create a simple `license-category.routes.ts` that reads from `LicenseCategoryModel` \n2. Map BE model to FE format\n3. For now, populate with defaults (type based on code: A1→Xe máy, others→Ô tô, etc.)\n4. In the future, could add more fields\n\nBut actually, let me look at this differently. The user said \"hạng bằng trong hệ thống đã có\" - meaning the data is already in the `licensecategories` collection. I just need to:\n1. Create an API to expose this data\n2. Update FE to call this API\n\nFor the FE fields not in BE (`fee`, `tags`, `inactive`, `dat`), I'll use defaults for now. The user can edit them later.\n\nNow I'm planning the full implementation: create the necessary files for the backend routes and controller, set up the frontend service to fetch from the new endpoint, and update the settings page to use it. I also need to check the existing repository structure to follow the same patterns.","thinkingSignature":"b2eb77c2f68da6da89b0a30565abb6a33cce82c078cec3427f4ca38c3d68beb8"},{"type":"text","text":"Rõ rồi. Vấn đề: database có collection `licensecategories` (từ seed) nhưng **không có API** để FE đọc. FE đang đọc từ `settings.license_categories` — vốn trống. Fix bằng cách tạo API mới.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gqm1loz97n5r_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/repositories/settings.repository.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":839,"output":651,"cacheRead":44485,"cacheWrite":874,"totalTokens":46849,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776050663345,"responseId":"062b94e8e59cc19072b4783a0e488dfb"}}
{"type":"message","id":"a9d7ec45","parentId":"6ff89532","timestamp":"2026-04-13T03:24:42.387Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gqm1loz97n5r_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { ISettingsRepository } from '@/domain/repositories/settings.repository.interface';\nimport { Settings } from '@/domain/entities/settings.entity';\nimport SettingsModel from '@/infrastructure/database/models/settings.model';\n\nexport class SettingsRepository implements ISettingsRepository {\n  async findByUserId(userId: string): Promise<Settings | null> {\n    const settings = await SettingsModel.findOne({ userId });\n    if (!settings) return null;\n    const obj = settings.toObject({ getters: true, virtuals: true, versionKey: false });\n    return {\n      ...obj,\n      id: obj._id.toString(),\n      createdAt: obj.createdAt,\n      updatedAt: obj.updatedAt,\n    } as unknown as Settings;\n  }\n\n  async update(userId: string, data: Partial<Omit<Settings, 'id'>>): Promise<Settings | null> {\n    const settings = await SettingsModel.findOneAndUpdate({ userId }, data, { new: true, upsert: true });\n    const obj = settings.toObject({ getters: true, virtuals: true, versionKey: false });\n    return {\n      ...obj,\n      id: obj._id.toString(),\n      createdAt: obj.createdAt,\n      updatedAt: obj.updatedAt,\n    } as unknown as Settings;\n  }\n\n  async create(data: Omit<Settings, 'id' | 'createdAt' | 'updatedAt'>): Promise<Settings> {\n    const settings = await SettingsModel.create(data);\n    const obj = settings.toObject({ getters: true, virtuals: true, versionKey: false });\n    return {\n      ...obj,\n      id: obj._id.toString(),\n      createdAt: obj.createdAt,\n      updatedAt: obj.updatedAt,\n    } as unknown as Settings;\n  }\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776050682295}}
{"type":"message","id":"dfa3c6ee","parentId":"a9d7ec45","timestamp":"2026-04-13T03:24:55.166Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me create all the needed files:\n\n1. BE: Create `license-category` route, controller, service, repository\n2. FE: Create `licenseCategoryService.ts`, update `settings/page.tsx`\n\nLet me write all the files now.","thinkingSignature":"3d02d752cabb323a78563b0ef75c1fdbcba4b9df2da94c9f7e705a22207c898b"},{"type":"text","text":"Bây giờ tạo đồng thời cả BE lẫn FE:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0rmofasjcdvh_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/application/services/license-category.service.ts","content":"import { LicenseCategoryModel } from '@/infrastructure/database/models/license_category.model';\n\nexport class LicenseCategoryService {\n  async findAll(): Promise<any[]> {\n    const docs = await LicenseCategoryModel.find({}).sort({ code: 1 }).lean();\n    return docs.map(doc => ({\n      id: (doc._id as any).toString(),\n      code: doc.code,\n      name: doc.name,\n      description: doc.description || '',\n      type: this.inferType(doc.code),\n      fee: '',\n      tags: [],\n      inactive: [],\n      dat: null,\n    }));\n  }\n\n  private inferType(code: string): 'Ô tô' | 'Xe máy' {\n    if (['A', 'A1', 'A2', 'A3', 'A4'].includes(code)) return 'Xe máy';\n    return 'Ô tô';\n  }\n}\n"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0rmofasjcdvh_2","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/interface/controllers/license-category.controller.ts","content":"import { Request, Response } from 'express';\nimport { LicenseCategoryService } from '@/application/services/license-category.service';\nimport { catchAsync } from '@/interface/middlewares/catchAsync.middleware';\n\nconst service = new LicenseCategoryService();\n\nexport const getAll = catchAsync(async (_req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const categories = await service.findAll();\n  res.status(200).json({ success: true, data: categories });\n});\n"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0rmofasjcdvh_3","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be/src/interface/routes/license-category.routes.ts","content":"import express from 'express';\nimport * as controller from '@/interface/controllers/license-category.controller';\n\nconst router = express.Router();\nrouter.get('/', controller.getAll);\n\nexport default router;\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":492,"output":572,"cacheRead":45163,"cacheWrite":1581,"totalTokens":47808,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776050682394,"responseId":"062b94fb12a78ce73e0616efd1cebc0d"}}
